-*- outline -*-

This is the dlvhex-GoogleCalendar ActionAddon, an addon for 'dlvhex-actionplugin'.

This file contains information on compiling and installing and using the 
rdfplugin.

* Dependencies
dlvhex-GoogleCalendar ActionAddon depends on the following:

** dlvhex
http://www.kr.tuwien.ac.at/research/systems/dlvhex/

* Building the dlvhex-GoogleCalendar ActionAddon

** Prerequisites

*** dlvhex
See dlvhex installation instructions at:
http://www.kr.tuwien.ac.at/research/systems/dlvhex/download.html

*** Google Calendar Data API (Java)

See
http://code.google.com/apis/calendar/data/2.0/developers_guide_java.html

** Building

The typical procedure to build is:

./configure
make
make install

Additionally, you will need to be have the following files in your $CLASSPATH:

* gdata-core-1.0.jar: provided in gdata-src.java-1.40.3.zip\gdata\java\lib
* gdata-calendar-2.0.jar: provided in gdata-src.java-1.40.3.zip\gdata\java\lib
* google-collect-1.0-rc1.jar: provided in gdata-src.java-1.40.3.zip/gdata/java/deps
* jsr305.jar: provided in gdata-src.java-1.40.3.zip/gdata/java/deps
* calendarApp.class: provided in the src/ subdirectory of GCal Action Addon
 
Some more information for each step follows:

*** Configuration

`./configure --enable-userinstall' will install the addon to the users home
folder i.e.`~/.dlvhex/plugins'. By default the addon will be installed
in the DLVPATH/lib/dlvhex/plugins.

General configuration options and explanation of related environment variables
can be found using
`./configure --help'

** Installation
Run `make install' to install dlvhex-GoogleCalendar ActionAddon into a system-wide
plugin directory provided by dlvhex.
